{
  "text": "Mammalian NAGS is found in the mitochondrial matrix of cells of the liver and intestines but not the kidney or spleen [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , and has been purified to apparent homogeneity from rat and human liver [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . The molecular weight of the human holoenzyme is 190,000. Human liver NAGS affinity constants (Km) were reported as 4.4 mM for acetyl-CoA and 8.1 mM for L-glutamate [CITATION_5] , quite different from the values of 0.7 and 1 mM, respectively, for the rat enzyme [CITATION_6] . The later numbers are in better agreement with recent biochemical studies on the recombinant enzymes [CITATION_7] .",
